procedures:
Let the buffer run out until all the cells flow into the sample reservoir.
Once the cell suspension has completely entered the elutriation chamber, close the injection valve.
Refer to the procedure in Table 1[href=https://www.wicell.org#tbl1] for cell collection.
Note: Just before the suspension lowers down to the bottom of the syringe, turn the bypass valve back toward the syringe to stop the sample flow. This will prevent any air bubbles from entering the line.
Start fraction collection (Table 1[href=https://www.wicell.org#tbl1]):
Fraction 1 (pump: 13.4 mL/min; elutriator: 3000 rpm): Collect four 50 mL tubes (200 mL in total): Major cell population-elongating spermatids ;
Fraction 2 (pump: 18.2 mL/min; elutriator: 3000 rpm): Collect two 50 mL tubes (100 mL in total): Major cell population-elongating spermatids;
Fraction 3 (pump: 23.6 mL/min; elutriator: 3000 rpm): Collect two 50 mL tubes (100 mL in total): Major cell population- elongating spermatids and round spermatids;
Fraction 4 (pump: 19.6 mL/min; elutriator: 2250 rpm): Collect three 50 mL tubes (150 mL in total): Major cell population-round spermatids;
Fraction 5 (pump: 21 mL/min; elutriator: 2250 rpm): Collect two 50 mL tubes (100 mL in total): Major cell population-round spermatids;
Fraction 6 (pump: 23.6 mL/min; elutriator: 2250 rpm): Collect two 50 mL tubes (100 mL in total): Major cell population-round spermatids;
Fraction 7 (pump: 34 mL/min; elutriator: 2250 rpm): Collect three 50 mL tubes (150 mL in total): Major cell population- round spermatids and pachytene spermatocytes;
Fraction 8 (pump: 40.5 mL/min; elutriator: 2250 rpm): Collect three 50 mL tubes (150 mL in total): Major cell population-pachytene spermatocytes.
Fraction 9 (pump: 45 mL/min; elutriator: 2250 rpm): Collect two 50 mL tubes (100 mL in total): Major cell population-pachytene spermatocytes.
